Name: PyMailMan
Version: 0.4
Summary: A simple tool for sending mail by Python
Home-page: UNKNOWN
Author: kongkongyzt
Author-email: kongkongyzt@gmail.com
License: MIT License
Description: PyMailMan
        =========
        
        Project homepage
        ----------------
        
        https://github.com/kongkongyzt/PyMailMan
        
        Install
        -------
        
        .. code:: sh
        
            sudo pip install PyMailMan
        
        Usage
        -----
        
        -  To send the text
        
        .. code:: python
        
            from PyMailMan import PyMailMan
        
            mail = PyMailMan(host='smtp.qq.com', user='12345678', password='12345678')
            mail.send(
                ['783087000@qq.com'], 
                'This is title', 
                'This is the content'
            )
            print 'OK' if mail.status else mail.errMsg
        
        -  To send the HTML
        
        .. code:: python
        
            from PyMailMan import PyMailMan
        
            mail = PyMailMan(host='smtp.qq.com', user='12345678', password='12345678')
            mail.send(
                ['783087000@qq.com'],
                'This is title', 
                "<p style='color:red'>This is the content</p>"
            )
            print 'OK' if mail.status else mail.errMsg
        
        -  To send the email with file
        
        .. code:: python
        
            from PyMailMan import PyMailMan
        
            mail = PyMailMan(host='smtp.qq.com', user='12345678', password='12345678')
            #You need to write the absolute path of the file
            mail.send(
                ['783087000@qq.com'], 
                'This is title', 
                'This is the content',
                '/home/kongkongyzt/a.txt',
                '/home/kongkongyzt/b.txt'
            )
            print 'OK' if mail.status else mail.errMsg
        
Keywords: mail
Platform: any
